		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">How about "Faceball 1985"?</div>
<br />This was a gameboy game right? The first raycaster ever?
<br />
<br />Well, I played that demo (sicn.nes). It's nice to finally see a raycaster done for the NES. Mine is taking too long to get finished but at least now I can rest knowing that maybe it is because I'm implementing so many more features. The most difficult thing to get rid of was the block that shouldn't show but it does when you move towards a corner (happens a lot in this demo). The solution was quite simple, but took a very long time to figure out. The other pain in the ass was figuring out how to remove the "fisheye" (distorted walls) effect without adding too much extra complexity.
<br />
<br />Anyway, I shouldn't be saying those things without a demo in my hands, should I? =)

		

