	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Talking about 3D effects... What about scaling and rotating sprites on the NES ? It would take a few pattern table space and a few code for each scanling/rotating sprite.
<br />I think scanling isn't too hard. Using the trick to have 16-bit counter and une only the high 8 bits as the pixel index should work fine.
<br />Rotating would be pretty undoable to what I currently know. Any ideas ?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


