		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Very few non-Super-FX games even on the Super NES used real-time sprite scaling or rotation. In fact, <em>Yoshi's Island</em> seems to use the Super FX chip primarily for just that, by drawing sprites as texture-mapped quads.

		

